{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-mdx-frontmatter-type-mdx-frontmatter-slug-js-content-file-path-content-docs-responsive-examples-object-fit-mdx","path":"/docs/object-fit/","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"id":"0f502d4e-8892-5d5e-ab43-0f36e1e725df","body":"\r\nimport { Paragraph } from \"../../../src/components/Mdx/textComponents\"\r\nimport CodeWrapper from \"../../../src/components/Mdx/CodeWrapper\"\r\nimport CatImg from \"../../../src/images/cat-resized.png\"\r\n\r\n# Object Fit\r\n\r\n#### How to use Object Fit\r\n\r\nThere are a few different classes for Object Fit:\r\n\r\n| Class             | CSS rule                |\r\n| :---------------- | :---------------------- |\r\n| object-contain    | object-fit: contain;    |\r\n| object-cover      | object-fit: cover;      |\r\n| object-fill       | object-fit: fill;       |\r\n| object-none       | object-fit: none;       |\r\n| object-scale-down | object-fit: scale-down; |\r\n\r\nLet's look at a few examples. In each example, a perfectly square cat-imge is being put into a rectangular container:\r\n\r\n<div className=\"center p-lg\">\r\n  <figure>\r\n    <img src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n    <figcaption>\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"text-lg py-md align-center\"\r\n        text=\"Origonal Img 512x512\"\r\n      />\r\n    </figcaption>\r\n  </figure>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div className=\"row gap-lg max-mob:max-h-16 max-h-16 lg:max-h-20 lg:mb-2xl\">\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9 center p-xl sizing-border\">\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"text-lg py-md align-center\"\r\n        text=\"In each case, the above square photo has been fit into this not-quite-so-square container!\"\r\n      />\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img className=\"w-full h-full object-fill\" src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <Paragraph\r\n          className=\"text-lg py-md\"\r\n          text=\"object-fit: fill; (default)\"\r\n        />\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div className=\"row gap-lg max-mob:max-h-16 max-h-16 lg:max-h-20 lg:mb-2xl\">\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img className=\"w-full h-full object-contain\" src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <Paragraph\r\n          className=\"text-lg py-md\"\r\n          text=\"object-fit: contain\"\r\n        />\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img className=\"w-full h-full object-cover\" src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <Paragraph\r\n          className=\"text-lg py-md\"\r\n          text=\"object-fit: cover;\"\r\n        />\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div className=\"row gap-lg max-mob:max-h-16 max-h-16 lg:max-h-24\">\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img className=\"w-full h-full object-none\" src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <Paragraph className=\"text-lg py-md\" text=\"object-fit: none\" />\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img\r\n          className=\"w-full h-full object-scale-down\"\r\n          src={CatImg}\r\n          alt=\"Cat\"\r\n        />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <Paragraph className=\"text-lg py-md\" text=\"object-fit: scale-down\" />\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nYou'll notice `contain` and `scale-down` look similar, because `scale-down` looks at either `contain` and `cover` and chosses the smallest version. Here, `contain` is smaller, so it chooses that to size the image.\r\n\r\nOn larger sizes, `cover` looks like `none`, that's becasue `none` doesn't resize the image, and as the screen gets bigger (somewhere around 1400px for this size) the `cover` image size actually gets close enough to the natural 512px width of the image to where it starts to match.\r\n\r\nAnd for `object-fit: fill` it's easy to see shows how it's been stretched out by the broweser. TAll images are sized to width:100% and height 100% of it's container (aspect ration 16/9) but the object-fit property has significant effects on how it's presented!\r\n\r\nHere is the html for the last row:\r\n\r\n<CodeWrapper title=\"HTML\" >\r\n\r\n```HTML\r\n<!-- the <img> tags recieve the object-fit classes: -->\r\n<div class=\"row gap-lg max-mob:max-h-16 max-h-16 lg:max-h-24\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div class=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img class=\"w-full h-full object-none\" src={CatImg} alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <p class=\"text-lg py-md\">object-fit: none</p>\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <figure>\r\n      <div class=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n        <img\r\n          class=\"w-full h-full object-scale-down\"\r\n          src={CatImg}\r\n          alt=\"Cat\"\r\n        />\r\n      </div>\r\n      <figcaption>\r\n        <p class=\"text-lg py-md\">object-fit: scale-down</p>\r\n      </figcaption>\r\n    </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n</CodeWrapper>\r\n\r\nAnd yes these classes are responsive too. As just an example, here's the image changing it's object-fit in response to various screen widths. If you're on a browser you can resize the screen (might have to close the sidebar on small widths):\r\n\r\n<div className=\"mb-xl center h-20\">\r\n  <figure>\r\n    <div className=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n      <img\r\n        className=\"w-full h-full \r\n\t\t\t\tlg:object-fill\r\n\t\t\t\tscr:object-cover\r\n\t\t\t\ttab:object-contain\r\n\t\t\t\tobject-none\r\n\t\t\t\"\r\n        src=\"/static/cat-resized-2ec747eea85cbd774bc0c06734ec57d8.png\"\r\n        alt=\"Cat\"\r\n      />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <figcaption>\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"align-center text-lg display-none radius-md lg:display-block\"\r\n        text=\"Break Point: lg Object-fit: fill (default)\"\r\n      />\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"align-center text-lg display-none scr:display-block lg:display-none\"\r\n        text=\"Break Point: scr Object-fit: cover\"\r\n      />\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"align-center text-lg display-none tab:display-block scr:display-none\"\r\n        text=\"Break Point: tab  ( < 768px ) Object-fit: contain;\"\r\n      />\r\n      <Paragraph\r\n        className=\"align-center text-lg display-block tab:display-none\"\r\n        text=\"Break Point: max-mob ( < 640px ) Object-fit: none;\"\r\n      />\r\n    </figcaption>\r\n\r\n  </figure>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nAnd here's the HTML:\r\n\r\n<CodeWrapper title=\"HTML\" >\r\n\r\n```HTML\r\n<div class=\"mb-xl center h-20\">\r\n  <figure>\r\n    <div class=\"border-lg border-dashed bg-background-dkr ratio-16/9\">\r\n      <img\r\n        class=\"w-full h-full\r\n          lg:object-fill\r\n          scr:object-cover\r\n          tab:object-contain\r\n          object-none\"\r\n        src=\"/static/cat-resized-2ec747eea85cbd774bc0c06734ec57d8.png\"\r\n        alt=\"Cat\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <figcaption>\r\n      <!-- caption text here -->\r\n    </figcaption>\r\n  </figure>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n</CodeWrapper>\r\n\r\nSo that wraps it for Object-fit. Happy Coding!\r\n","frontmatter":{"description":"Overview of Object Fit","title":"Object Fit","type":"docs","image":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"0f502d4e-8892-5d5e-ab43-0f36e1e725df","frontmatter__type":"docs","frontmatter__slug":"object-fit","__params":{"frontmatter__type":"docs","frontmatter__slug":"object-fit"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Object Fit","tags":["responsive","box-sizing"],"type":"docs","description":"Overview of Object Fit","category":"responsive","slug":"object-fit","order":140}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2241216091"],"slicesMap":{}}